File creation task 1:

Create a directory called ""my_folder"", navigate into it, and create a file named ""my_file.txt"" with some text.
Then, create another file named ""another_file.txt"" with some text.
Concatenate the content of ""another_file.txt"" to ""my_file.txt"" and display the updated content.
Finally, list all files and directories in the current directory


I created the "my_folder" directory

$> mkdir my_folder


navigating to "my_folder" directory

$> cd my_folder


created a file "my_file.txt" with "Welcome"

$> echo "Welcome" > my_file.txt


created a file "another_file.txt" with "All"

$> echo "All" > another_file.txt


Concatenated the "another_file.txt" to "my_file.txt"

$> cat another_file.txt >> my_file.txt


Display the updated content 

$> cat my_file.txt


Listed all directories and files

$> ls -ltrh

